{"parse":{"title":"Thomas Ferebee","pageid":4394952,"revid":860286427,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em;width:25.5em;border-spacing:2px;\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color:#C3D6EF;\"><span class=\"fn\">Thomas Wilson Ferebee</span></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;border-bottom: 1px solid #aaa;; line-height: 1.5em\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Van_Kirk_Tibbets,_and_Ferebee.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Van Kirk Tibbets, and Ferebee.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Van_Kirk_Tibbets%2C_and_Ferebee.jpg/275px-Van_Kirk_Tibbets%2C_and_Ferebee.jpg\" width=\"275\" height=\"206\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Van_Kirk_Tibbets%2C_and_Ferebee.jpg/413px-Van_Kirk_Tibbets%2C_and_Ferebee.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Van_Kirk_Tibbets%2C_and_Ferebee.jpg/550px-Van_Kirk_Tibbets%2C_and_Ferebee.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"707\" data-file-height=\"530\" /></a><div style=\"font-size: 100%\"><a href=\"/wiki/Theodore_Van_Kirk\" title=\"Theodore Van Kirk\">Van Kirk</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Paul_Tibbets\" title=\"Paul Tibbets\">Tibbets</a>, and Thomas Ferebee (right)</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right: 1em\">Born</th><td>\n<span style=\"display:none\">(<span class=\"bday\">1918-11-09</span>)</span>November 9, 1918<br /><a href=\"/wiki/Mocksville,_North_Carolina\" title=\"Mocksville, North Carolina\">Mocksville, North Carolina</a>, U.S.</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right: 1em\">Died</th><td>\nMarch 16, 2000<span style=\"display:none\">(2000-03-16)</span> (aged&#160;81)<br /><a href=\"/wiki/Windermere,_Florida\" title=\"Windermere, Florida\">Windermere, Florida</a>, U.S.</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right: 1em\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<span class=\"flagicon\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/Flag_of_the_United_States_%28Pantone%29.svg/23px-Flag_of_the_United_States_%28Pantone%29.svg.png\" width=\"23\" height=\"12\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/Flag_of_the_United_States_%28Pantone%29.svg/35px-Flag_of_the_United_States_%28Pantone%29.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/Flag_of_the_United_States_%28Pantone%29.svg/46px-Flag_of_the_United_States_%28Pantone%29.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1235\" data-file-height=\"650\" />&#160;</span>United States</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right: 1em\">Service/<wbr />branch</th><td>\n<span class=\"flagicon\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/Flag_of_the_United_States_Air_Force.svg/23px-Flag_of_the_United_States_Air_Force.svg.png\" width=\"23\" height=\"14\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/Flag_of_the_United_States_Air_Force.svg/35px-Flag_of_the_United_States_Air_Force.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/Flag_of_the_United_States_Air_Force.svg/46px-Flag_of_the_United_States_Air_Force.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1024\" data-file-height=\"614\" />&#160;</span><a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Air_Force\" title=\"United States Air Force\">United States Air Force</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right: 1em\">Years&#160;of service</th><td>\n1942\u20131970</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right: 1em\">Rank</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Colonel_(United_States)\" title=\"Colonel (United States)\">Colonel</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right: 1em\">Unit</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/509th_Composite_Group\" title=\"509th Composite Group\">509th Composite Group</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right: 1em\">Battles/wars</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/World_War_II\" title=\"World War II\">World War II</a></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/Vietnam_War\" title=\"Vietnam War\">Vietnam War</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right: 1em\">Awards</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Silver_Star\" title=\"Silver Star\">Silver Star</a></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/Air_Medal\" title=\"Air Medal\">Air Medal</a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Thomas Wilson Ferebee</b> (November 9, 1918 &#8211; March 16, 2000) was the <a href=\"/wiki/Bombardier_(air_force)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bombardier (air force)\">bombardier</a> aboard the <a href=\"/wiki/B-29_Superfortress\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"B-29 Superfortress\">B-29 Superfortress</a>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Enola_Gay\" title=\"Enola Gay\">Enola Gay</a></i>, which dropped the <a href=\"/wiki/Atomic_bomb\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Atomic bomb\">atomic bomb</a>, \"<a href=\"/wiki/Little_Boy\" title=\"Little Boy\">Little Boy</a>\", on <a href=\"/wiki/Hiroshima\" title=\"Hiroshima\">Hiroshima</a> in 1945.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Biography\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Biography</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Bibliography\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Bibliography</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Biography\">Biography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Thomas_Ferebee&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Biography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Thomas Wilson Ferebee was born on a farm outside <a href=\"/wiki/Mocksville,_North_Carolina\" title=\"Mocksville, North Carolina\">Mocksville, North Carolina</a>, as the third of eleven children. In 1935, at age 17, he attended <a href=\"/wiki/Lees-McRae_College\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lees-McRae College\">Lees-McRae College</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Banner_Elk,_NC\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Banner Elk, NC\">Banner Elk, NC</a>. Talented in athletics since childhood, he earned awards in <a href=\"/wiki/Track_and_field\" title=\"Track and field\">track</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Basketball\" title=\"Basketball\">basketball</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/American_football\" title=\"American football\">football</a>. After training for a small position with the <a href=\"/wiki/Boston_Red_Sox\" title=\"Boston Red Sox\">Boston Red Sox</a> and not making the team, he joined the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Army\" title=\"United States Army\">Army</a>. A knee injury kept him from service in the <a href=\"/wiki/Infantry\" title=\"Infantry\">infantry</a> but he was accepted into flight training. After two years of <a href=\"/wiki/Flight_school\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Flight school\">flight school</a>, Ferebee was assigned as a bombardier in the <a href=\"/wiki/European_Theater_of_Operations\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"European Theater of Operations\">European theater</a>, completing more than 60 bombing missions. In the summer of 1944, he was recruited by <a href=\"/wiki/Colonel\" title=\"Colonel\">Colonel</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Paul_Tibbets\" title=\"Paul Tibbets\">Paul Tibbets</a> to be part of the <a href=\"/wiki/509th_Composite_Group\" title=\"509th Composite Group\">509th Composite Group</a> which was formed to drop the <a href=\"/wiki/Atomic_bomb\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Atomic bomb\">atomic bomb</a>. After the war, he remained in the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Air_Force\" title=\"United States Air Force\">Air Force</a> until December 1970. After he retired from the Air Force, he worked as a real estate agent in and around <a href=\"/wiki/Orlando,_Florida\" title=\"Orlando, Florida\">Orlando, Florida</a>. Like Tibbets, Ferebee never expressed regret for his role in the bombing, saying \"it was a job that had to be done.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Like Tibbets, Ferebee remained in the military in the years after World War II as the <a href=\"/wiki/U.S._Army_Air_Forces\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"U.S. Army Air Forces\">U.S. Army Air Forces</a> became the <a href=\"/wiki/U.S._Air_Force\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"U.S. Air Force\">U.S. Air Force</a>. Ferebee spent most of his USAF career in the <a href=\"/wiki/Strategic_Air_Command\" title=\"Strategic Air Command\">Strategic Air Command</a>, serving during the <a href=\"/wiki/Cold_War\" title=\"Cold War\">Cold War</a> and in Vietnam. He retired from the U.S. Air Force as a <a href=\"/wiki/Combat_Systems_Officer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Combat Systems Officer\">master navigator</a> (bombardier) with the rank of <a href=\"/wiki/Colonel\" title=\"Colonel\">colonel</a>. He died at his home in <a href=\"/wiki/Windermere,_Florida\" title=\"Windermere, Florida\">Windermere, Florida</a> at the age of 81.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He was survived by his wife, Mary Ann Ferebee, who donated his collection of military documents and objects to the <a href=\"/wiki/North_Carolina_Museum_of_History\" title=\"North Carolina Museum of History\">North Carolina Museum of History</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Raleigh,_North_Carolina\" title=\"Raleigh, North Carolina\">Raleigh</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Salisbury_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Salisbury-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Thomas_Ferebee&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"navigation\" aria-label=\"Portals\" class=\"noprint portal plainlist tright\" style=\"margin:0.5em 0 0.5em 1em;border:solid #aaa 1px\">\n<ul style=\"display:table;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0.1em;max-width:175px;background:#f9f9f9;font-size:85%;line-height:110%;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold\">\n<li style=\"display:table-row\"><span style=\"display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center\"><img alt=\"seal\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Seal_of_the_United_States_Department_of_the_Air_Force.svg/28px-Seal_of_the_United_States_Department_of_the_Air_Force.svg.png\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Seal_of_the_United_States_Department_of_the_Air_Force.svg/42px-Seal_of_the_United_States_Department_of_the_Air_Force.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Seal_of_the_United_States_Department_of_the_Air_Force.svg/56px-Seal_of_the_United_States_Department_of_the_Air_Force.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"356\" data-file-height=\"356\" /></span><span style=\"display:table-cell;padding:0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em;vertical-align:middle\"><a href=\"/wiki/Portal:United_States_Air_Force\" title=\"Portal:United States Air Force\">United States Air Force portal</a></span></l